OL,6,F"Some worry that they've been briefed
OL,7,Fagainst to the newspapers, and
OL,8,Fgenerally speaking, they worry about
OL,9,Fthe dilution that ... Lord Storey has
OL,10,Fwarned against."
OL,12,FLord Ponsonby said he was "sorry to
OL,13,Fhear that", adding: "I am aware of
OL,14,Fvery recent interaction with the
OL,15,Ffamilies in Liverpool, and what I
OL,16,Funderstand is those talks have been
OL,17,Fgoing positively, and it is very much
OL,18,Fhoped that we able to reach some form
OL,19,Fof agreement in the coming weeks and
OL,20,Fmonths."
